        [
          "You were one of the 'bad kids' at the reservation school - only because you missed your family and deeply resented the attempts of your white teachers to impose their Christianity on you. You were fostered out to a white Mormon family whom you grew to hate for how all of them just quietly presumed to be better than you. You might have killed them, or maybe yourself, except you had attracted the attention of your sire. He liked your spark, and so brought you over. But you find plenty to resent in the Sabbat as well - from the teeming hordes who assume you just have to be Gangrel because you're Navajo, or even your sire, whose Mormon beliefs tells him you're not Navajo, you're cryto-Jewish. As a rejection of the expectations placed on you, you've delved deeply into a study of the Abyss. You know that this, according to the stories you heard in childhood of unspeakable beasts who fed on the flesh of their own, has damned you completely. And that's a price you're willing to pay, as long as you can take some assholes out with you before it's your turn to go."
